{"type":"text","timestamp":1775876901613,"sessionID":"ses_2857d2699ffecO620o5FW4sVCc","part":{"id":"prt_d7a82ecd1001swZP7Kyt8HDI9t","messageID":"msg_d7a82da4e001oYWZle0NkSqr3w","sessionID":"ses_2857d2699ffecO620o5FW4sVCc","type":"text","text":"Let me explore the project structure and context first.","time":{"start":1775876901612,"end":1775876901612}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877060896,"sessionID":"ses_2857d2699ffecO620o5FW4sVCc","part":{"id":"prt_d7a82efec001ZpihW3p5cXAQKV","messageID":"msg_d7a82da4e001oYWZle0NkSqr3w","sessionID":"ses_2857d2699ffecO620o5FW4sVCc","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_e7db3888553c45e18a212a58","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - what directories exist, what the project does\n2. Any existing Makefile or build system\n3. Any existing design docs, specs, or AR (Architecture Request) documents\n4. The \"root\" module - what it contains\n5. Any previous stages (ST-1) related to AR-033\n6. Package.json, go.mod, or other dependency files to understand the tech stack\n7. Any existing patterns for design.md files in the project\n\nSearch for:\n- Any Makefile files\n- Any design.md or DESIGN.md files\n- Any AR-*.md or specs files\n- The project root structure\n- Any documentation about the build system\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of the project structure, existing build system, and any relevant context for writing a design.md about a Makefile build target system.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2857cf541ffe11Rd3KJBJ8KO8Q (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is a comprehensive summary of the AgentCube project based on my thorough exploration:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Summary\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n**AgentCube** is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents (Go module: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`). It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic through session-aware proxies, and manages lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n#### Root-level directories:\n```\n(project root)/\n├── cmd/                    # Go binary entrypoints (5 binaries)\n│   ├── router/             # HTTP reverse proxy / session router\n│   ├── workloadmanager/    # K8s controller for sandbox lifecycle\n│   ├── agentd/             # Idle cleanup controller\n│   ├── picod/              # Sandbox-internal code execution daemon\n│   └── cli/                # Python CLI tool (Typer-based)\n├── pkg/                    # Shared Go packages (7 packages)\n│   ├── apis/               # CRD type definitions (runtime + agents groups)\n│   ├── router/             # Router logic\n│   ├── workloadmanager/    # WM controller + handlers + reconciler\n│   ├── agentd/             # AgentD reconciler\n│   ├── picod/              # PicoD server + file operations\n│   ├── store/              # Session store (Redis/Valkey)\n│   └── common/             # Shared types\n├── client-go/              # Generated K8s typed clients, informers, listers\n├── docker/                 # Dockerfiles (3 images)\n│   ├── Dockerfile          # WorkloadManager\n│   ├── Dockerfile.router   # Router\n│   ├── Dockerfile.picod    # PicoD\n│   └── .dockerignore\n├── manifests/charts/base/  # Helm chart\n├── test/                   # Test scripts (chart render, e2e)\n├── testing/                # TDD manifest\n├── changes/                # AR-001 through AR-033 (Architecture Requests)\n├── ci-cd/                  # CI/CD design + spec docs\n├── code-execution/         # PicoD design + spec\n├── session-routing/        # Router design + spec\n├── session-store/          # Session store design + spec\n├── idle-cleanup/           # AgentD design + spec\n├── deployment/             # Deployment design + spec\n├── integrations/           # Integrations design + spec\n├── cli-toolkit/            # CLI toolkit design + spec\n├── python-sdk/             # Python SDK design + spec\n├── go.mod / go.sum         # Go module definition (Go 1.25.0)\n├── design.md               # Root-level design doc (actually AR-029 content)\n├── delta-spec.md           # Root-level delta spec (AR-029)\n├── proposal.md             # Root-level proposal (AR-028)\n├── tasks.md                # Root-level tasks (AR-023)\n├── project.md              # Project context document\n└── coverage.out            # Go coverage output\n```\n\n### 2. Existing Makefile / Build System\n\n**There is NO Makefile currently in the project root.** This is explicitly stated in the AR-033 proposal:\n\n> \"项目无任何 Makefile。开发者需要记忆并手动执行分散的命令\"\n\nHowever, the **upstream reference project** (`/tmp/agentcube-ref`) does have a Makefile with targets referenced by CI/CD workflows:\n- `docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod`\n- `docker-buildx-push`, `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod`\n- `e2e`, `e2e-clean`\n- `lint`\n- `gen-check`, `gen-copyright`\n- `gen-all`, `generate`, `gen-client`, `gen-crd`\n\nThe current working copy has **zero Makefile files** anywhere in the tree (confirmed by glob search).\n\n### 3. Design Docs, Specs, and AR Documents\n\n#### AR (Architecture Request) Pattern:\nEach AR lives in `changes/AR-NNN/` and contains exactly 4 files:\n- `proposal.md` -- Purpose, scope, impact analysis, alternatives, status\n- `design.md` -- Architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing, implementation steps, follow-up changes\n- `delta-spec.md` -- Gherkin-style requirements with Given/When/Then scenarios\n- `tasks.md` -- Implementation task breakdown with dependency graphs\n\nThere are **33 ARs** (AR-001 through AR-033). AR-033 is the current one about the Makefile build target system.\n\n#### Feature-level design docs (outside changes/):\n- `ci-cd/design.md`, `ci-cd/spec.md`\n- `code-execution/design.md`, `code-execution/spec.md`\n- `session-routing/design.md`, `session-routing/spec.md`\n- `session-store/design.md`\n- `idle-cleanup/design.md`, `idle-cleanup/spec.md`\n- `deployment/design.md`\n- `integrations/design.md`\n- `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n- `python-sdk/design.md`\n\n### 4. The \"root\" Module\n\nThe **root module** refers to the project root level (not a Go package). AR-033 is scoped to `Module: root` and `Language: Makefile`. It is the only AR targeting the project root itself rather than a specific subcomponent. The root module contains:\n- `go.mod` / `go.sum` (Go module definition)\n- All `cmd/` and `pkg/` source code\n- `docker/`, `manifests/`, `test/`, `testing/` directories\n- All top-level markdown files\n\n### 5. AR-033 (Current Stage)\n\nAR-033 is titled **\"Makefile 构建目标体系\"** (Makefile Build Target System). Its current state:\n\n| File | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| `proposal.md` | **Complete** -- Detailed scope, in/out of scope, architecture summary, impact analysis, alternatives considered |\n| `design.md` | **Skeleton only** -- Has section headers but all content is `<!-- TODO -->` placeholders |\n| `delta-spec.md` | **Complete** -- 358 lines of detailed Gherkin-style requirements covering all targets |\n| `tasks.md` | **Skeleton only** -- Has headers but all content is `<!-- TODO -->` placeholders |\n\nThe proposal defines these target categories:\n- **Go Build:** `build`, `build/<binary>` (router, workloadmanager, agentd, picod), `clean`\n- **Docker:** `docker`, `docker/<image>` (agentcube, router, picod)\n- **Test:** `test`, `test-coverage`, `test-chart`\n- **Code Quality:** `lint`, `fmt`, `vet`\n- **Helm:** `helm-lint`, `helm-template`\n- **Python:** `python-lint`, `python-test`\n- **Composite:** `all` (build + test + lint), `ci` (build + test + test-coverage + lint + helm-lint)\n\n### 6. Tech Stack (from go.mod and project.md)\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| **Go version** | 1.25.0 |\n| **Module** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| **HTTP framework** | Gin v1.10.0 |\n| **Kubernetes** | k8s.io/api v0.34.1, controller-runtime v0.22.2 |\n| **Cache/Store** | go-redis/v9 v9.18.0, valkey-go v1.0.73 |\n| **Auth** | golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.2 |\n| **Metrics** | prometheus/client_golang v1.22.0 |\n| **Testing** | stretchr/testify v1.11.1 |\n| **Python SDK** | Python >= 3.10, requests, PyJWT, cryptography |\n| **Packaging** | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions |\n\n### 7. design.md File Patterns\n\nThe project has a **consistent design.md template** used across all ARs. The standard structure is:\n\n```markdown\n# AR-NNN: <Title> -- Design/设计说明\n\n## 1. 架构 (Architecture)\n### 1.1 定位 (Purpose/Positioning)\n### 1.2 目录结构 (Directory Layout) -- Before/After\n### 1.3 依赖关系 (Dependencies)\n\n## 2. 数据结构 (Data Structures)\n\n## 3. API 契约 (API Contracts)\n\n## 4. 错误处理 (Error Handling)\n\n## 5. 测试策略 (Testing Strategy)\n\n## 6. 实现步骤 (Implementation Steps)\n\n## 7. 后续变更 (Follow-up Changes)\n```\n\nKey patterns observed:\n- Section headers are bilingual (Chinese/English)\n- Architecture section includes ASCII diagrams, directory trees, dependency graphs\n- Data structures include Go structs, tables, and relationship diagrams\n- API contracts include endpoint tables with Method/Path/Body/Response\n- Error handling includes scenario tables\n- Testing strategy includes test categories, key scenarios, and mocking strategies\n- Implementation steps are numbered tables with file actions and prerequisites\n- Follow-up changes are dependency tables\n\nThe most detailed examples are **AR-001** (636 lines, CRD type definition) and **AR-032** (506 lines, Dockerfile multi-stage builds). The AR-033 design.md is currently a 57-line skeleton with all TODO placeholders.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2857cf541ffe11Rd3KJBJ8KO8Q","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project","time":{"start":1775876901563,"end":1775877060893}}}}
